bubbleParent.description: Indicates if the proxy will bubble an event to its parent.

apiName.description: The name of the API that this proxy corresponds to.

accessibilityHidden.description: Whether the view should be "hidden" from (i.e., ignored by) the accessibility service.

accessibilityHint.description: Briefly describes what performing an action (such as a click) on the view will do.

accessibilityValue.description: A string describing the value (if any) of the view for the device's accessibility service.

animatedCenter.description: Current position of the view during an animation.

backgroundDisabledColor.description: Disabled background color of the view, as a color name or hex triplet.

backgroundRepeat.description: Determines whether to tile a background across a view.

backgroundLeftCap.description: Size of the left end cap.

backgroundTopCap.description: Size of the top end cap.

borderColor.description: Border color of the view, as a color name or hex triplet.

children.description: Array of this view's child views.

filterTouchesWhenObscured.description: Discards touch related events if another app's system overlay covers the view.

focusable.description: Whether view should be focusable while navigating with the trackball.

hiddenBehavior.description: Sets the behavior when hiding an object to release or keep the free space

overrideCurrentAnimation.description: When on, animate call overrides current animation if applicable.

pullBackgroundColor.description: Background color of the wrapper view when this view is used as either Titanium.UI.ListView.pullView or Titanium.UI.TableView.headerPullView. Defaults to undefined. Results in a light grey background color on the wrapper view.

rotation.description: Clockwise 2D rotation of the view in degrees.

rotationX.description: Clockwise rotation of the view in degrees (x-axis).

rotationY.description: Clockwise rotation of the view in degrees (y-axis).

scaleX.description: Scaling of the view in x-axis in pixels.

scaleY.description: Scaling of the view in y-axis in pixels.

softKeyboardOnFocus.description: Determines keyboard behavior when this view is focused. Defaults to Titanium.UI.Android.SOFT_KEYBOARD_DEFAULT_ON_FOCUS.

touchEnabled.description: Determines whether view should receive touch events.

touchFeedback.description: A material design visual construct that provides an instantaneous visual confirmation of touch point.

touchFeedbackColor.description: Optional touch feedback ripple color. This has no effect unless touchFeedback is true.

translationX.description: Horizontal location of the view relative to its left position in pixels.

translationY.description: Vertical location of the view relative to its top position in pixels.

translationZ.description: Depth of the view relative to its elevation in pixels.

transitionName.description: A name to identify this view in activity transition.

viewShadowRadius.description: Determines the blur radius used to create the shadow.

viewShadowColor.description: Determines the color of the shadow.

viewShadowOffset.description: Determines the offset for the shadow of the view.

horizontalWrap.description: Determines whether the layout has wrapping behavior.

keepScreenOn.description: Determines whether to keep the device screen on.

OS_ANDROID.description: A special constant that is replaced during the app build with a boolean true/false value.

OS_IOS.description: A special constant that is replaced during the app build with a boolean true/false value.

OS_VERSION_MAJOR.description: The operation system's major version number.

OS_VERSION_MINOR.description: The operating system's minor version number.

OS_VERSION_PATCH.description: The operating system's patch version number.

ENV_DEVELOPMENT.description: A special constant that is replaced during the app build with a boolean true/false value, based on whether deploy type is 'development'. Typically true for simulator/emulator builds.

ENV_PRODUCTION.description: A special constant that is replaced during the app build with a boolean true/false value, based on whether deploy type is 'production'. Typically true for app store/ad-hoc builds.

ENV_TEST.description: A special constant that is replaced during the app build with a boolean true/false value, based on whether deploy type is 'test'. Typically true for device builds.

DIST_ADHOC.description: A special constant that is replaced during the app build with a boolean true/false value, based on whether build target is 'dist-adhoc'.

DIST_STORE.description: A special constant that is replaced during the app build with a boolean true/false value, based on whether build target is 'dist-appstore' or 'dist-playstore'.

localeMatcher.description: The locale matching algorithm to use.

usage.description: Indicates if the comparison is for sorting or searching when matching strings.

sensitivity.description: Indicates how characters should be compared.

ignorePunctuation.description: Indicates if punctuation characters should be ignored during the compare.

numeric.description: Indicates if numbers in string should be compared as integers.

caseFirst.description: Indicates if upper case or lower case characters should sort first.

dateStyle.description: Specifies the locale's built-in month, day, and year formatting styles.

timeStyle.description: Specifies the locale's built-in hour, minute, and second formatting styles.

fractionalSecondDigits.description: Number of millisecond digits to show. Valid values are 0-3.

dayPeriod.description: Indicates how the AM/PM time component should be shown.

timeZone.description: The time zone the Date object's value should be converted to when formatted.

hour12.description: Indicates if formatter should output to either 12-hour or 24-hour time.

hourCycle.description: Indicates how the hour should be formatted.

formatMatcher.description: The format matching algorithm to use.

weekday.description: Indicates how a weekday name should be shown.

era.description: Indicates how the era name, such as AD or BC, should be shown.

year.description: Indicates how the year should be formatted.

month.description: Indicates how the month should be formatted.

day.description: Indicates how the numeric day should be formatted.

hour.description: Indicates how the hour should be formatted.

minute.description: Indicates how minutes should be formatted.

second.description: Indicates how seconds should be formatted.

timeZoneName.description: Indicates how the time zone should be shown.

currency.description: Set to the ISO 4217 currency code to use when formatting with the currency style.

currencyDisplay.description: Indicates how the currency symbol or name should be shown.

useGrouping.description: Indicates if grouping separators should be displayed.

minimumIntegerDigits.description: Applies leading zeros to the integer portion of the formatted number.

minimumFractionDigits.description: Applies trailing zeros in fractional portion of the formatted number.

maximumFractionDigits.description: Max number of fractional digits to be shown. Will round at this max digit.

maximumSignificantDigits.description: Max number of significant digits to be shown. Will round at this max digit.

notation.description: Indicates if number should be formatted to scientific or engineering notation.

generatedMessage.description: Indicates if the message was auto-generated (true) or not.

poolSize.description: This is the size (in bytes) of pre-allocated internal Buffer instances used for pooling. This value may be modified.

INSPECT_MAX_BYTES.description: The maximum number of bytes that will be returned when buf.inspect() is called. This can be overridden by user modules.

kMaxLength.description: The largest size allowed for a single buffer.Buffer instance.

defaultMaxListeners.description: The default number of maximum listeners for all EventEmitters

O_RDONLY.description: Flag indicating to open a file for read-only access.

O_WRONLY.description: Flag indicating to open a file for write-only access.

O_RDWR.description: Flag indicating to open a file for read-write access.

S_IFMT.description: Bit mask used to extract the file type code.

S_IFREG.description: File type constant for a regular file.

S_IFDIR.description: File type constant for a directory.

S_IFCHR.description: File type constant for a character-oriented device file.

S_IFBLK.description: File type constant for a block-oriented device file.

S_IFIFO.description: File type constant for a FIFO/pipe.

S_IFLNK.description: File type constant for a symbolic link.

S_IFSOCK.description: File type constant for a socket.

O_CREAT.description: Flag indicating to create the file if it does not already exist.

O_EXCL.description: Flag indicating that opening a file should fail if the O_CREAT flag is set and the file already exists.

O_NOCTTY.description: Flag indicating that if path identifies a terminal device, opening the path shall not cause that terminal to become the controlling terminal for the process (if the process does not already have one).

O_TRUNC.description: Flag indicating that if the file exists and is a regular file, and the file is opened successfully for write access, its length shall be truncated to zero.

O_APPEND.description: Flag indicating that data will be appended to the end of the file.

O_DIRECTORY.description: Flag indicating that the open should fail if the path is not a directory.

O_NOFOLLOW.description: Flag indicating that the open should fail if the path is a symbolic link.

O_SYNC.description: Flag indicating that the file is opened for synchronized I/O with write operations waiting for file integrity.

O_DSYNC.description: Flag indicating that the file is opened for synchronized I/O with write operations waiting for data integrity.

O_SYMLINK.description: Flag indicating to open the symbolic link itself rather than the resource it is pointing to.

O_NONBLOCK.description: Flag indicating to open the file in nonblocking mode when possible.

S_IRWXU.description: File mode indicating readable, writable, and executable by owner.

S_IRUSR.description: File mode indicating readable by owner.

S_IWUSR.description: File mode indicating writable by owner.

S_IXUSR.description: File mode indicating executable by owner.

S_IRWXG.description: File mode indicating readable, writable, and executable by group.

S_IRGRP.description: File mode indicating readable by group.

S_IWGRP.description: File mode indicating writable by group.

S_IXGRP.description: File mode indicating executable by group.

S_IRWXO.description: File mode indicating readable, writable, and executable by others.

S_IROTH.description: File mode indicating readable by others.

S_IWOTH.description: File mode indicating writable by others.

S_IXOTH.description: File mode indicating executable by others.

F_OK.description: Flag indicating that the file is visible to the calling process. This is useful for determining if a file exists, but says nothing about rwx permissions. Default if no mode is specified.

R_OK.description: Flag indicating that the file can be read by the calling process.

W_OK.description: Flag indicating that the file can be written by the calling process.

X_OK.description: Flag indicating that the file can be executed by the calling process. This has no effect on Windows (will behave like fs.constants.F_OK).

COPYFILE_EXCL.description: The copy operation will fail if dest already exists.

dev.description: The numeric identifier of the device containing the file. Always returns 0 on Titanium.

ino.description: The file system specific "Inode" number for the file. Always returns 0 on Titanium.

nlink.description: The number of hard-links that exist for the file. Always returns 0 on Titanium.

rdev.description: A numeric device identifier if the file represents a device. Always returns 0 on Titanium.

blksize.description: The file system block size for i/o operations. Hard-coded to 4096 on Titanium right now.

blocks.description: The number of blocks allocated for this file.

atimeMs.description: The timestamp indicating the last time this file was accessed expressed in milliseconds since the POSIX Epoch.

mtimeMs.description: The timestamp indicating the last time this file was modified expressed in milliseconds since the POSIX Epoch.

ctimeMs.description: The timestamp indicating the last time the file status was changed expressed in milliseconds since the POSIX Epoch.

birthtimeMs.description: The timestamp indicating the creation time of this file expressed in milliseconds since the POSIX Epoch.

flag.description: See support of file system flags.

withFileTypes.description: If true, the results will be returned as fs.Dirents

force.description: When true, exceptions will be ignored if path does not exist.

maxRetries.description: If an EBUSY, EMFILE, ENFILE, ENOTEMPTY, or EPERM error is encountered, Node.js will retry the operation with a linear backoff wait of retryDelay milliseconds longer on each try. This option represents the number of retries. This option is ignored if the recursive option is not true.

retryDelay.description: The amount of time in milliseconds to wait between retries. This option is ignored if the recursive option is not true.

bigint.description: Whether the numeric values in the returned fs.Stats object should be bigint.

EOL.description: The operating system-specific end-of-line marker. \n on POSIX \r\n on Windows

PRIORITY_BELOW_NORMAL.description: The process scheduling priority above PRIORITY_LOW and below PRIORITY_NORMAL.

PRIORITY_ABOVE_NORMAL.description: The process scheduling priority above PRIORITY_NORMAL and below PRIORITY_HIGH.

user.description: The number of milliseconds the CPU has spent in user mode.

nice.description: The number of milliseconds the CPU has spent in nice mode.

sys.description: The number of milliseconds the CPU has spent in sys mode.

irq.description: The number of milliseconds the CPU has spent in irq mode.

delimiter.description: Provides the platform-specific path delimiter: ; for Windows : for POSIX

sep.description:
Provides the platform-specific path segment separator:
  • \ on Windows
  • / on POSIX

root.description: Root filesystem path, i.e. '/' or 'C:\\'. Ignored if pathObject.dir is provided

ext.description: file extension, i.e. '.txt'. Ignored if pathObject.base exists

arch.description: Returns the operating system CPU architecture for which the binary was compiled. Possible values are return 'arm', 'arm64', 'ia32', 'x64', 'mips', and 'unknown'. The return value is equivalent to os.arch. Relates strongly to Titanium.Platform.architecture.

argv.description: The process.argv property returns an array containing the command-line arguments passed when the Node.js process was launched. The first element will be process.execPath. See process.argv0 if access to the original value of argv[0] is needed. The second element will be the path to the JavaScript file being executed. The remaining elements will be any additional command-line arguments.

argv0.description: The process.argv0 property stores a read-only copy of the original value of argv[0] passed when Node.js starts.

debugPort.description: The port used by the debugger when enabled.

noDeprecation.description: The process.noDeprecation property indicates whether the --no-deprecation flag is set on the current Node.js process. See the documentation for the 'warning' event and the emitWarning() method for more information about this flag's behavior.

pid.description: The process.pid property returns the PID of the process. Always returns 0 in Titanium.

ppid.description: The process.ppid property returns the PID of the parent of the current process. Always returns 0 in Titanium.

throwDeprecation.description: The initial value of process.throwDeprecation indicates whether the --throw-deprecation flag is set on the current Node.js process. process.throwDeprecation is mutable, so whether or not deprecation warnings result in errors may be altered at runtime. See the documentation for the 'warning' event and the emitWarning() method for more information.

traceDeprecation.description: The process.traceDeprecation property indicates whether the --trace-deprecation flag is set on the current Node.js process. See the documentation for the 'warning' event and the emitWarning() method for more information about this flag's behavior.

detail.description: Additional text to include with the error.

showHidden.description: If true, object's non-enumerable symbols and properties are included in the formatted result. WeakMap and WeakSet entries are also included as well as user defined prototype properties (excluding method properties).

depth.description: Specifies the number of times to recurse while formatting object. This is useful for inspecting large objects. To recurse up to the maximum call stack size pass Infinity or null.

customInspect.description: If false, [util.inspect.custom](depth, opts) functions are not invoked.

showProxy.description: If true, Proxy inspection includes the target and handler objects.

maxArrayLength.description: Specifies the maximum number of Array, TypedArray, WeakMap and WeakSet elements to include when formatting. Set to null or Infinity to show all elements. Set to 0 or negative to show no elements.

maxStringLength.description: Specifies the maximum number of characters to include when formatting. Set to null or Infinity to show all elements. Set to 0 or negative to show no characters.

breakLength.description: The length at which input values are split across multiple lines. Set to Infinity to format the input as a single line (in combination with compact set to true or any number >= 1).

compact.description: Setting this to false causes each object key to be displayed on a new line. It will also add new lines to text that is longer than breakLength. If set to a number, the most n inner elements are united on a single line as long as all properties fit into breakLength. Short array elements are also grouped together. No text will be reduced below 16 characters, no matter the breakLength size. For more information, see the example below.

sorted.description: If set to true or a function, all properties of an object, and Set and Map entries are sorted in the resulting string. If set to true the default sort is used. If set to a function, it is used as a compare function.

getters.description: If set to true, getters are inspected. If set to 'get', only getters without a corresponding setter are inspected. If set to 'set', only getters with a corresponding setter are inspected. This might cause side effects depending on the getter function.

displayHomeAsUp.description: Displays an "up" affordance on the "home" area of the action bar.

homeAsUpIndicator.description: Sets a custom icon for the "home" button in the corner of the action bar.

homeButtonEnabled.description: Enable or disable the "home" button in the corner of the action bar.

requestedOrientation.description: Specifies a specific orientation for this activity.

requestCode.description: Unique, automatically generated integer request code.

resultCode.description: Integer result code that the started activity passed to setResult.

ACTION_ATTACH_DATA.description: Used to indicate that the data is an attachment.

ACTION_BATTERY_CHANGED.description: Listen to battery state change status.

ACTION_BATTERY_OKAY.description: Inidicates the battery is now okay after being low.

ACTION_BOOT_COMPLETED.description: Indicates the system has finished booting.

ACTION_BUG_REPORT.description: Show activity for reporting a bug.

ACTION_CALL.description: Perform a call to someone specified by the data property.

ACTION_CLOSE_SYSTEM_DIALOGS.description: User dismissed a temporary system dialog, such as the notification drawer or recent-app drawer.

ACTION_DEVICE_STORAGE_LOW.description: Indicates a low memory condition on the device.

ACTION_DIAL.description: Dial a number specified by the Intent's data property.

ACTION_GET_CONTENT.description: Allow the user to select a particular kind of data specified by the Intent's type property.

ACTION_HEADSET_PLUG.description: A wired headset has been plugged in or unplugged.

CATEGORY_EMBED.description: Activity can run inside a parent activity.

EXTRA_BCC.description: String array containing e-mail addresses for blind carbon copying.

EXTRA_CC.description: String array containing e-mail addresses for carbon copying.

EXTRA_DATA_REMOVED.description: Boolean indicating full uninstall (true) or partial uninstall (false).

EXTRA_DONT_KILL_APP.description: Boolean indicating to restart the application or not.

EXTRA_INTENT.description: An Intent describing the choices you would like shown.

EXTRA_TEMPLATE.description: Initial data to place in a newly created record.

FLAG_ACTIVITY_CLEAR_TOP.description: If the activity is present, removes any activities on top of it to make it the foreground activity.

FLAG_ACTIVITY_EXCLUDE_FROM_RECENTS.description: Exclude the activity from recently launched activities.

FLAG_ACTIVITY_FORWARD_RESULT.description: Return result to the original calling activity.

FLAG_ACTIVITY_MULTIPLE_TASK.description: Start the activity as a new task even if it exists.

FLAG_ACTIVITY_NEW_TASK.description: Activity will be the start of a new task (collection of activities).

FLAG_ACTIVITY_NO_HISTORY.description: Do not keep the activity in the history stack.

FLAG_ACTIVITY_REORDER_TO_FRONT.description: If the activity already exists, place it at the top of the history stack.

FLAG_ACTIVITY_RESET_TASK_IF_NEEDED.description: If the task already exists, resets the task to its initial state.

FLAG_ACTIVITY_SINGLE_TOP.description: Do not launch the activity if it is already running.

FLAG_DEBUG_LOG_RESOLUTION.description: Enable a log message to print out the resolution of the intent.

FLAG_FROM_BACKGROUND.description: Indicates the intent is coming from a background operation.

FLAG_GRANT_READ_URI_PERMISSION.description: Grant read permission on the URI in the Intent's data or clipboard.

FLAG_RECEIVER_REGISTERED_ONLY.description: When sending a broadcast, only registered receivers will be called.

FLAG_CANCEL_CURRENT.description: Cancel the current pending intent before creating a new one.

FLAG_NO_CREATE.description: If the current intent does not exist, do not create it.

FLAG_ONE_SHOT.description: The pending intent can only be used once.

FLAG_UPDATE_CURRENT.description: If the current pending intent already exists, only update the current intent's extra data.

CATEGORY_CALL.description:

communication request.

CATEGORY_EMAIL.description: Notification category indicating an asynchronous bulk message (email).

CATEGORY_EVENT.description: Notification category indicating a calendar event.

Use for urgent or time-critical notifications, for example, turn-by-turn directions or
emergency alerts.

PRIORITY_DEFAULT.description: Default priority if it does not fit into another priority category.

VISIBILITY_SECRET.description: Shows the most minimal information of the notification on the lockscreen.

WAKE_LOCK_FULL.description: Ensures that the screen and keyboard backlight are on at full brightness.

WAKE_LOCK_SCREEN_BRIGHT.description: Ensures that the screen is on at full brightness; the keyboard backlight will be allowed to go off.

WAKE_LOCK_ACQUIRE_CAUSES_WAKEUP.description: Turn the screen on when the wake lock is acquired.

WAKE_LOCK_ON_AFTER_RELEASE.description: When this wake lock is released, poke the user activity timer so the screen stays on for a little longer.

RESULT_CANCELED.description: Used with setResult to specify that an activity was canceled.

RESULT_FIRST_USER.description: Used with setResult to specify a user-defined result.

RESULT_OK.description: Used with setResult to specify that an activity succeeded.

SCREEN_ORIENTATION_BEHIND.description: Use with requestedOrientation to specify the activity should run in the same orientation as the activity behind it in the activity stack.

SCREEN_ORIENTATION_LANDSCAPE.description: Use with requestedOrientation to specify a landscape screen orientation.

SCREEN_ORIENTATION_NOSENSOR.description: Use with requestedOrientation to specify that the sensor should be ignored and the display should not rotate.

dialog in iTunes.

regardless of its age or expiration date.

CACHE_POLICY_RETURN_CACHE_DATA_DONT_LOAD.description:
Specifies that the existing cache data should be used to satisfy a request,
regardless of its age or expiration date.

SELECTION_GRANULARITY_DYNAMIC.description: Selection granularity varies automatically depending on the selection.

SELECTION_GRANULARITY_CHARACTER.description: Selection endpoints can be placed at any character boundary.

INJECTION_TIME_DOCUMENT_START.description: Inject the script after the document element is created, but before any other content is loaded.

INJECTION_TIME_DOCUMENT_END.description: Inject the script after the document finishes loading, but before other subresources finish loading.

weight.description: The symbol weight to use for the SF Symbol. Can be one of ultralight, light, thin, normal, semibold, bold, heavy or black.

passthroughViews.description: Passthrough views to use when the popover is shown.

POPOVER_ARROW_DIRECTION_ANY.description: An arrow that points in any direction.

POPOVER_ARROW_DIRECTION_LEFT.description: An arrow that points toward the left.

POPOVER_ARROW_DIRECTION_RIGHT.description: An arrow that points toward the right.

POPOVER_ARROW_DIRECTION_UNKNOWN.description: The status of the arrow is currently unknown.

activationState.description: Returns the current activation state of the watch.

ACTIVATION_STATE_NOT_ACTIVATED.description: The watch is currently not activated.

hasContentPending.description: Returns true if there is more content for the session to deliver.

remainingComplicationUserInfoTransfers.description: The number of calls remaining to transferCurrentComplication before the system starts transferring the complicationUserInfo as regular userInfos.

isSupported.description: Returns true if the device supports watch connectivity.

isPaired.description: Returns true if the device is paired with a watch.

isWatchAppInstalled.description: Returns true if the accompanying watch app is installed.

isComplicationEnabled.description: Returns true if complication is enabled on the installed watch app.

isReachable.description: Returns true if the watch is currently reachable.

isActivated.description: Returns true if the watch is currently activated.

ELEMENT_NODE.description: Used with nodeType to identify an Element node.

ATTRIBUTE_NODE.description: Used with nodeType to identify an Attr node.

TEXT_NODE.description: Used with nodeType to identify a Text node.

CDATA_SECTION_NODE.description: Used with nodeType to identify a CDATASection node.

ENTITY_REFERENCE_NODE.description: Used with nodeType to identify an EntityReference node.

ENTITY_NODE.description: Used with nodeType to identify an Entity node.

PROCESSING_INSTRUCTION_NODE.description: Used with nodeType to identify a ProcessingInstruction node.

COMMENT_NODE.description: Used with nodeType to identify a Comment node.

DOCUMENT_NODE.description: Used with nodeType to identify a Document node.

DOCUMENT_TYPE_NODE.description: Used with nodeType to identify a DocumentType node.

DOCUMENT_FRAGMENT_NODE.description: Used with nodeType to identify a DocumentFragment node.

NOTATION_NODE.description: Used with nodeType to identify a Notation node.

textContent.description: Content (value) of all text nodes within this node.

localName.description: Local part of the qualified name of this node.

specified.description: True if this attribute was explicitly given a value in the instance document, false otherwise.

internalSubset.description: The internal subset as a string.

tagName.description: The name of the element, as defined by its tag.

notationName.description: For unparsed entities, the name of the notation for the entity. For parsed entities, this is null.

target.description: Retrieve the target of this processing instruction. XML defines this as being the first token following the markup that begins the processing instruction.
